# VFX Graph (strict)

## Policy

- **All new effects** use **VFX Graph** (`.vfx`) + **`VisualEffect`** component.
- **Forbidden** in `Assets/Game/`: new `ParticleSystem`, `LineRenderer`, `TrailRenderer` for gameplay/VFX (legacy modules only via engine; not project content).
- Runtime spawn: [`VisualEffectSpawner`](Assets/Game/Scripts/Runtime/Gameplay/Vfx/VisualEffectSpawner.cs) or pooled `VisualEffect` prefabs.

## Paths

| Asset | Folder |
|-------|--------|
| Graphs | `Assets/Game/Art/VFX/` |
| Prefabs | `Assets/Game/Prefabs/Effects/` |

MCP `vfx_create_asset` and agents: use **`Assets/Game/Art/VFX/`**, not default `Assets/VFX/`.

## URP

- Package: `com.unity.visualeffectgraph@17.5.0` with URP 17.5
- Graphics Settings → URP asset assigned (`Assets/Game/Settings/Rendering/RPAsset.asset`)
- Test effects in **Play Mode** after graph or parameter changes

## MCP

- Activate group: **`vfx`** → `manage_vfx`, `manage_shader`, `manage_texture`
- VFX Graph: **`vfx_*` actions only** (`vfx_create_asset`, `vfx_assign_asset`, `vfx_set_exposed`, `vfx_play`, …)
- Shaders / procedural textures: `manage_shader`, `manage_texture` (same **vfx** group)
- **Do not use `particle_*`, `line_*`, `trail_*`** in this project
- Ignore outdated MCP header comment about HDRP-only; this template is URP + VFX Graph

## Code

- Assembly: `Game.Gameplay` → `Unity.VisualEffectGraph.Runtime`
- `using UnityEngine.VFX;`

